---
description: API route rules
globs: app/api/**, src/app/api/**
alwaysApply: false
---
Route → Controller → Service → Repository strictly.
Validate session before any DB access via @supabase/ssr.
Rate limit: check lib/config/limits.ts.
Return { success, data?, error? } always.
Never expose raw Supabase errors to client.

# SUPABASE GENERATED COLUMNS
Never INSERT into generated columns (e.g. violation_count, shortfall_idr).
Never manually calculate values that Postgres computes automatically.
Always SELECT generated columns directly — Supabase returns them.
Before any INSERT, check the migration file for GENERATED ALWAYS AS columns.
If shortfall_idr or similar columns appear GENERATED in migrations:
- INSERT only the inputs (month_number, year, violations JSON, etc.)
- SELECT the computed column back after INSERT
- NEVER calculate it in API code